WEBVTT

00:00:01.110 --> 00:00:03.150
Young children are very busy.

00:00:03.720 --> 00:00:05.850
They love playing
and experimenting

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:08.220
to find out about the
world around them.

00:00:09.150 --> 00:00:11.940
Your child needs you and
the other people in her life

00:00:12.090 --> 00:00:13.800
to help her make
sense of it all.

00:00:15.990 --> 00:00:18.988
That's because your child learns
about the world through interaction.

00:00:20.070 --> 00:00:23.580
It's all about the simple everyday
things you do with your child.

00:00:24.120 --> 00:00:27.720
Like eating together ,
talking and playing .

00:00:27.901 --> 00:00:32.100
the most important thing about these
everyday interactions is the back and forth

00:00:32.130 --> 00:00:33.510
between your child and you.

00:00:34.440 --> 00:00:35.100
The talk.

00:00:35.462 --> 00:00:36.462
Smiles.

00:00:36.691 --> 00:00:37.470
Cuddles

00:00:37.710 --> 00:00:38.850
the playing together.

00:00:39.480 --> 00:00:43.380
This stimulates your child's
brain and makes her feel loved.

00:00:43.710 --> 00:00:48.030
These interactions give your child confidence
and build connections in her brain.

00:00:48.390 --> 00:00:49.980
Which help her develop thinking,

00:00:50.280 --> 00:00:50.940
Social,

00:00:51.060 --> 00:00:52.350
,and emotional skills.

00:00:53.220 --> 00:00:56.550
As your child is becoming more
determined to do things for himself.

00:00:56.940 --> 00:00:59.130
Your support and
encouragement of vital.

00:01:00.060 --> 00:01:02.780
They give your child the
confidence to try new things,

00:01:02.805 --> 00:01:04.265
like taking her clothes off

00:01:04.290 --> 00:01:05.460
,cleaning teeth.

00:01:05.790 --> 00:01:08.730
Or exploring during play

00:01:09.150 --> 00:01:12.780
Encouraging her effort and being
specific about what it is she's doing.

00:01:13.170 --> 00:01:16.530
Gives her confidence to try
again when things don't go right.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:20.010
Spending time outside together

00:01:20.160 --> 00:01:24.106
gives your child the chance to explore
the environment and have adventures.

00:01:25.020 --> 00:01:27.960
She has more space and
freedom for physical play.

00:01:28.320 --> 00:01:29.320
Like crawling

00:01:29.550 --> 00:01:30.090
running.

00:01:30.480 --> 00:01:31.480
Jumping.

00:01:31.620 --> 00:01:32.700
Kicking and throwing.

00:01:33.300 --> 00:01:35.010
This is good for
your child's health

00:01:35.220 --> 00:01:36.450
physical development

00:01:36.570 --> 00:01:37.620
and confidence.

00:01:38.250 --> 00:01:39.029
Singing

00:01:39.210 --> 00:01:39.990
dancing

00:01:40.110 --> 00:01:43.080
and listening to music are
lots of fun for your child.

00:01:43.770 --> 00:01:47.340
These activities help her be
creative and express feelings.

00:01:48.060 --> 00:01:51.568
Singing encourages him to use
words and develop his memory.

00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:55.860
Dancing develops groth
motor skills and coordination.

00:01:56.370 --> 00:01:58.650
Whether she keeps time
with the music or not.

00:01:59.400 --> 00:02:02.790
And quietly listening to
music can be great downtime

00:02:02.896 --> 00:02:04.140
for your busy child.

00:02:05.160 --> 00:02:07.620
Your child is an
amazing learner.

00:02:08.370 --> 00:02:12.900
She's learning new things all the time
through the everyday things you do together.

00:02:13.950 --> 00:02:15.990
Interacting with her
in simple ways.

00:02:16.440 --> 00:02:17.440
Like talking.

00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:18.700
Listening.

00:02:18.840 --> 00:02:20.130
Singing and playing.

00:02:20.795 --> 00:02:22.740
Helps her grow and thrive.